Homecare is work, whose time and investment is weighing down the Turkana woman, and that must sink for an equal society to be birthed.To an indigenous Turkana woman, life is a hand-to-mouth affair. The Covid-19 pandemic has depressed incomes and upended lives globally. Governments have activated various responses to pull through the pandemic, especially for businesses.
But the response design must be rethought to favour the informal women traders.
Generally, women have disproportionately borne the brunt of the losses across the business spectrum. And there’s seems a sense of neglect, overtly or covertly by authorities. The debate around the disproportionate effects of Covid-19 on women seems a wrapped episode.



