The composition we currently have in both county and national governments, are a mere decoration, flowers, in the name of women representation.
I’m aware the county and national governments are currently mulling Covid-19 business cash distribution. It is important to consider realistic cash transfer models to be used in disbursing the funds.
There could be significant mobile telephony penetration in the county, but not to that monumental level. And even if that were the case, mobile money registration has been a challenge. Deep down the pastoral villages, marginalisation has been at a grand scale that a national identification card has been an alien term.
And so as the population struggles to integrate into the national registration “grid”, a more inclusive and hybrid approach entailing physical money distribution through the provincial administration and the government’s digital platform can effectively deliver the deal. After all, we are because they are, Ubuntu spirit must prevail.  He served in former president Daniel Moi's cabinet. BBI secretariat cleaned up the 5.2 million signatures that endorsed the Bill, and weeded out 800,000 that had entry irregularities. This comes days after he collapsed at a hotel in Nairobi and was placed under intensive care at Nairobi Hospital.